1️⃣ Concept Teaching (Strict, Clear, GATE-Oriented)
🔹 Random Experiment

An experiment whose outcome cannot be predicted with certainty.

Example:

Tossing a coin

Rolling a dice

🔹 Sample Space (S)

Set of all possible outcomes.

Example:

Coin toss → S = {H, T}

Dice → S = {1,2,3,4,5,6}

🔹 Event

Subset of sample space.

Example:
Even number on dice → {2,4,6}

